2026-06-07 | Find Profession in Special Family Tree

	Question
Return the profession of the person.
	Key Insight
Observe the transitions:
		Engineer (E)
		Left Child  -> E
		Right Child -> D
		Doctor (D)
		Left Child  -> D
		Right Child -> E
The profession changes only when we move to a right child.
Starting from the root Engineer:
		every right move flips profession
		every left move keeps profession same
The number of flips equals the number of 1-bits in:
		(pos - 1)
If number of set bits is:
		even → Engineer
		odd  → Doctor
	Approach
1.	Compute:
		x = pos - 1
2.	Count set bits in x.
3.	If count is even:
		return "Engineer"
4.	Otherwise:
		return "Doctor"
	Time Complexity
	O(log pos)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    string profession(int level, int pos) {
        int flips = __builtin_popcount(pos - 1);
        return (flips % 2 == 0)
               ? "Engineer"
               : "Doctor";
    }
};
	Why Does This Work?
Represent the path from root to position using:
		pos - 1
in binary.
Each bit represents:
		0 → left move
		1 → right move
Every right move flips the profession.
So:
		even number of right moves
		→ Engineer
		odd number of right moves
		→ Doctor
This gives a very elegant O(log pos) solution without constructing the tree.
